      "number": 1,
      "id": "PR_kwDOTTrAgM7v9udx",
      "title": "Remove nonce claim from OAT",
      "url": "https://github.com/gffletch/openid_authn_token/pull/1",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "josephdecock",
      "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "I'm not sure why the OAT carries the Source ID Token's `nonce` claim. The `nonce` is a request-response correlator between the Requesting Client and the OP. Is there a use case where a Target RP would need it?\r\n\r\nThis PR removes `nonce` from the OAT claims and adds a brief note in Security Considerations as a way to surface the question. My thinking is that session correlation and replay detection are already covered by `sid`, `jti`, `exp`, and proof-of-possession, but I may be missing something.",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-10T00:38:31Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-21T15:36:45Z",
      "baseRepository": "gffletch/openid_authn_token",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "3fdb6064673e0ccb8ec22d3d2125488db389e2b3",
      "headRepository": "josephdecock/openid_authn_token",
      "headRefName": "remove-nonce-from-oat",
      "headRefOid": "4e00930383a2621feabacf2f8f85faacbccc5bb8",
      "closedAt": "2026-07-21T15:36:45Z",
      "mergedAt": "2026-07-21T15:36:45Z",
      "mergedBy": "gffletch",
      "mergeCommit": {
        "oid": "42276f44e5182231d0437feec4068dcb7a02121a"
      },
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "gffletch",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "Thanks. This may have been a carry over from the way OpenID Key Binding is managing security. It is worth thinking through how the binding to session works. I\u2019ll go ahead and merge.",
